Troy Tech
April 24 at 12:54 PM Â·

Best U.S. High Schools: This week, the U.S. News & World Report released its 2020 High School Rankings. Troy is #213 of all high schools nationally, and #58 nationally in Magnet High Schools. In California, Troy is #26 of all high schools, and in Orange County Troy is #2. The U.S. News Best High Schools rankings include data on more than 24,000 public high schools in 50 states and the District of Columbia. Nearly 18,000 schools were ranked on six factors based on their performance on state assessments and how well they prepare students for college. https://www.usnews.com/education/best-high-schools/california/districts/fullerton-joint-union-high/troy-high-school-2247 #wearetroytech

Troy Tech
April 16 at 4:58 PM Â·

Today 4 Troy Tech Seniors and Troy Teacher Dave St. Clair received 2nd place in the state in the California Council on Economic Education's virtual personal finance competition. Shivana Anand, Soham Bose, Justin Lee, and Cassia Yeo had 90 minutes to create a financial plan for a fictitious client emphasizing short, mid and long term goals working together virtually using Zoom. The students created a wonderful and detailed Google slide presentation that they presented to the judges after lunch. It was a long day, but the judges were very impressed with our students. Great job Warriors! #wearetroytech

post_text:
From Troy High School:

Hello Warriors,
Here are some instructions as we move to online learning next week:
1. Please join your teacher's online classroom during the time you would be in that teacher's class
2. Teachers will electronically post instructions and assignments, including due dates and content
3. Please ensure you are completing assignments to the best of your ability and ask questions of your teacher
4. Teachers will be available during your normally scheduled class time for instruction and to answer questions and offer support with assignments

Thank you for your continued patience as we work online which is contributing to the safety of all our students and staff. We are Warriors!

Thank you for your continued patience as we work online which is contributing to the safety of all our students and staff. We are Warriors!

Please visit www.thetroydifference.org to register yourself for free and bid on these amazing auction items. We have exciting travel packages for spring break/college tour, spa and beauty baskets, restaurant gift cards, wine, and very unique experiences you can only find at our auction.

For example, one of our most popular items is VIP Graduation Seat Location. When senior families get their graduation tickets, they will have a chance to pick their preferred seats.

For more information, please email tso@thetroydifference.org. Help us raise money for our Troy students. Go Warriors!

Congratulations to the Troy Cybersecurity Program led by Mr. Allen Stubblefield. Four teams have qualified to compete at the National Cyberpatriot Championship in March.

We are also honored to have our very first cyber All-American, senior Charissa Kim, who has competed at Nationals for all 4 of her years at Troy! There have only been 6 other All-Americans in the 11 year history of the competition.

#thetroydifference @wearetroytech @troywarriors @troycyberdefense Troy Cyber Defense Booster Club

Congressional Medal of Honor Society
February 5 at 8:46 AM Â·

During Patriot Award Week 2020, the Congressional Medal of Honor Society connected with more than 250 Veterans during two Veteran Outreach Program (VOP) events in Los Angeles and Simi Valley, CA.

In Los Angeles (Bob Hope Patriotic Hall), MOH Recipients Charles Hagemeister, Thomas Kelley, and Gary Littrell discussed the challenges many Veterans face (mental health, transition, substance abuse, homelessness) and the resources available.

The VOP event in LA was moderated by Brig. Gen. (Ret) Ruth Wong, director of the L A County Dept. of Military and Veterans Affairs. JROTC cadets from Troy High School Navy JROTC and James Monroe High School Army JROTC programs posted the colors and engaged with MOH Recipients and Veterans.

More about the Congressional Medal of Honor Societyâ€™s programs and how you can support the legacy of the Medal of Honor at www.themedalofhonor.com.

Troy Tech/IB/Honors Testing for Current 8th Graders - REGISTRATION AVAILABLE NOW applicants.troyhigh.com Applicants are encouraged to register online between December 1, 2019 and January 22, 2020; however, applications are available at the testing and walk-ins are welcome. Your application will be processed upon the parent AND studentâ€™s sign-in on the test date.

Testing: January 11, 18, or 25, 2020 (select one) from 7:30-11:45 a.m. Check-in at North Gym 7:15 a.m. Bring student photo id or passport, printout of 8th grade schedule listing current math course, and a parent to sign documents. Testing covers mid-year eighth grade content in English and math. The test format is multiple choice questions and an English essay. The best preparation for testing is successful progress in a challenging eighth grade course of study. #wearetroytech

post_text:
Repost: Troy High NJROTC

Troy High School NJROTC was honored to host the return visit of CDR Lara Bollinger, USN, a 1998 graduate of Troy High School and one of the original members of the Troy High School NJROTC program. After high school, CDR Bollinger attended the University of San Diego, where she was commissioned through the NROTC program. CDR Bollinger currently served as the Public Affairs Officer for the Commander, Navy Recruiting Command in Memphis, TN. She engaged the Cadets in discussions ranging from Troy teachers and class work to Navy adventures and opportunities. Her visit was a success, as several cadets have now expressed an interest in serving our nation. @troyhighnjrotc #thetroydifference
